name: FACA Committee Management (FACA)
description: FACAP staff provide management and oversight of CDC FACs, including Special Emphasis Panels (SEPs). FACs and SEPs provide advice and recommendations on a broad range of issues affecting federal policies and programs. Every year the majority of CDC’s overall budget is distributed via contracts, grants, and cooperative agreements to affiliates throughout the world to promote health, prevent disease, injury and disability, and prepare for new health threats.  The committees and panel members are nominated by the applicable programs and SEPs are composed of subject matter experts (SMEs) that are appointed by the Secretary of HHS, CDC Director, World Trade Center Program Administrator, or President of the United States. The CDC Director appoints SEP reviewers. These SEP reviewers are convened in a panel to Team Project created automatically for FACA Committee Management (FACA) review applications and discuss and make initial funding recommendations to the programs. In Fiscal Year 2020, there are 19 FACs engaged with CDC, including the charter that governs the SEPs.

-- Create better accountability
-- Provision for system enhancements

- Business Value – 
-- Replace MACCS and MACCS-1350

-- Enhance user experience
-- Accurate Purchase card order processing and records management.

name: CDC Rapid Response Event System CRRES (CDCN2)
description: CDCResponder (CRRES)  - CDCResponder is a system that gathers response related information from the CDC workforce to assist with the coordination of staffing and deployment for emergency responses. The Response Management page provides the ability to view and manage responder-related staffing and deployment requests for an emergency response in a single, scrollable window with the ability to create an Event, Taskforce, Team, and Positions; and view positions, open positions, and active staff. The Response Management page can be used for data-driven analysis and metrics to assist in understanding staffing needs and perspective emergency response planning and projections.

name: FACA Committee Management (FACA)
description: FACAP staff provide management and oversight of CDC FACs, including Special Emphasis Panels (SEPs). FACs and SEPs provide advice and recommendations on a broad range of issues affecting federal policies and programs. Every year the majority of CDC’s overall budget is distributed via contracts, grants, and cooperative agreements to affiliates throughout the world to promote health, prevent disease, injury and disability, and prepare for new health threats.  The committees and panel members are nominated by the applicable programs and SEPs are composed of subject matter experts (SMEs) that are appointed by the Secretary of HHS, CDC Director, World Trade Center Program Administrator, or President of the United States. The CDC Director appoints SEP reviewers. These SEP reviewers are convened in a panel to Team Project created automatically for FACA Committee Management (FACA) review applications and discuss and make initial funding recommendations to the programs. In Fiscal Year 2020, there are 19 FACs engaged with CDC, including the charter that governs the SEPs.

name: FACA Committee Management (FACA)
description: FACAP staff provide management and oversight of CDC FACs, including Special Emphasis Panels (SEPs). FACs and SEPs provide advice and recommendations on a broad range of issues affecting federal policies and programs. Every year the majority of CDC’s overall budget is distributed via contracts, grants, and cooperative agreements to affiliates throughout the world to promote health, prevent disease, injury and disability, and prepare for new health threats.  The committees and panel members are nominated by the applicable programs and SEPs are composed of subject matter experts (SMEs) that are appointed by the Secretary of HHS, CDC Director, World Trade Center Program Administrator, or President of the United States. The CDC Director appoints SEP reviewers. These SEP reviewers are convened in a panel to Team Project created automatically for FACA Committee Management (FACA) review applications and discuss and make initial funding recommendations to the programs. In Fiscal Year 2020, there are 19 FACs engaged with CDC, including the charter that governs the SEPs.

name: Credit Card Purchasing System (CCPS)
description:
New system Credit Card Purchasing System (CCPS) is been developed by OFR and OCIO.
CCPS will replace MACCS and MACCS-1350 to better manage Purchase Card audits as well as enhance the user experience, resulting in more effective and accurate, purchase card order processing and records management.

Business Need & Business Value Summary: 
- Business need - 
-- Improve Order Lifecycle Management
-- Reduce financial risks
-- Create better accountability
-- Provision for system enhancements

- Business Value – 
-- Replace MACCS and MACCS-1350
-- Better enable the Purchase Card management of audits
-- Enhance user experience
-- Accurate Purchase card order processing and records management.

name: FACA Committee Management (FACA)
description: FACAP staff provide management and oversight of CDC FACs, including Special Emphasis Panels (SEPs). FACs and SEPs provide advice and recommendations on a broad range of issues affecting federal policies and programs. Every year the majority of CDC’s overall budget is distributed via contracts, grants, and cooperative agreements to affiliates throughout the world to promote health, prevent disease, injury and disability, and prepare for new health threats.  The committees and panel members are nominated by the applicable programs and SEPs are composed of subject matter experts (SMEs) that are appointed by the Secretary of HHS, CDC Director, World Trade Center Program Administrator, or President of the United States. The CDC Director appoints SEP reviewers. These SEP reviewers are convened in a panel to Team Project created automatically for FACA Committee Management (FACA) review applications and discuss and make initial funding recommendations to the programs. In Fiscal Year 2020, there are 19 FACs engaged with CDC, including the charter that governs the SEPs.
